<CHAPTER LBL="2"><TITLE><XREFTARGET ID="70448">xdkm</TITLE><SECTION1 LBL="" HELPID = "xdkmMainWindow"><TITLE>xdkm Main Window</TITLE><PARAGRAPH>This is the first window you see when you invoke <COMMAND>xdkm</COMMAND>: </PARAGRAPH>
<PARAGRAPH><FIGURE><GRAPHIC FILE="ch02.xdkm.gif" POSITION="INLINE" SCALE="FALSE"><CAPTION LBL="2-1"><PREFIX>Figure 2-1 </PREFIX>xdkm Main Window</CAPTION>
</FIGURE>
</PARAGRAPH>
<PARAGRAPH>All other <COMMAND>xdkm</COMMAND> windows are accessed through this one. The window consists of two parts: the menu bar and the display area. The menu bar provides options for operations on the disks shown in the display area. The display area shows you icons for all disks on the selected host.</PARAGRAPH>

